HEADWORD: guff
<hw>guff</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A ludicrously false
statment.</def> <wns>[wns=1]</wns>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> bullshit, bull, Irish bull, horseshit, shit, crap,
bunk, bunkum, buncombe, rot, hogwash, dogshit.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Insolent or disrespectful talk; <as>as, don't give
me any of your <ex>guff</ex>, young lady</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Guffaw</ent>⟦br⟧
